# Cursor Rules — home-lab Monorepo (dnd-app + bmo)

> Primary context file for Cursor AI. Reads on every invocation.
> For language/tool-specific rules, see also: AGENTS.md, CLAUDE.md

## Repository Structure (AI-first, flat, feature-based)

```
/home/patrick/home-lab/                    (monorepo root, live on Raspberry Pi 5)
├── dnd-app/                          Electron desktop VTT (TypeScript + React)
│   ├── src/                          NEVER restructure — electron-vite enforces main/preload/renderer/shared
│   │   ├── main/                     Electron main process (Node)
│   │   │   ├── ai/                   AI service layer
│   │   │   ├── ipc/                  IPC handlers (electron ↔ renderer)
│   │   │   ├── storage/              Persistent file storage
│   │   │   ├── plugins/              Game system plugin loader
│   │   │   ├── discord-integration/  Discord bot relay (for players)
│   │   │   └── bmo-bridge.ts         HTTP client to BMO Pi (port 5000)
│   │   ├── preload/                  Electron preload bridge
│   │   ├── renderer/                 React app (Vite) — keep feature-grouped
│   │   │   ├── src/components/       by feature: builder/, campaign/, game/, sheet/, lobby/, library/, levelup/, ui/
│   │   │   ├── src/services/         by feature: character/, chat-commands/, combat/, dice/, game-actions/, io/, library/, map/, plugin-system/
│   │   │   ├── src/stores/           zustand state stores
│   │   │   ├── src/pages/            route-level page components
│   │   │   ├── src/network/          peerjs multiplayer
│   │   │   └── public/data/5e/       D&D content as JSON (3000+ files)
│   │   └── shared/                   cross-process types/schemas
│   ├── scripts/                      CLI tooling, grouped by purpose
│   │   ├── build/                    runs via package.json (chunk-index, prerelease-clean)
│   │   ├── extract/                  PDF→JSON extraction pipeline
│   │   ├── generate/                 schema + batch generation
│   │   ├── submit/                   Anthropic Batch API submission
│   │   ├── audit/                    data validation (ultimate-audit.ts is canonical)
│   │   ├── batch-utils/              batch job monitors
│   │   ├── fix/                      one-off data migrations
│   │   └── schemas/                  zod schemas (shared by extract/)
│   ├── tools/                        dev utilities (run-audit.js, rename-to-kebab.js, etc.)
│   ├── docs/phases/                  30 planning docs (phase-NN-model.md)
│   ├── resources/                    app icons, installer
│   └── {package,tsconfig*,biome,vitest.config.ts,electron.vite.config.ts}  configs
│
├── bmo/                              Raspberry Pi voice assistant (Python + Flask)
│   ├── pi/                           Pi runtime code
│   │   ├── app.py                    main Flask entry (port 5000)
│   │   ├── agent.py                  main agent router entry
│   │   ├── cli.py                    CLI entry
│   │   ├── agents/                   41 specialized AI agents (base_agent, orchestrator, router, {alert,calendar,code,docs,...}_agent)
│   │   ├── services/                 service modules (calendar, weather, music, voice_pipeline, monitoring, etc.)
│   │   ├── hardware/                 Pi hardware drivers (fan_control, led_controller, oled_face, camera)
│   │   ├── bots/                     Discord bots — NAMED bots/ NOT discord/ (avoids discord.py shadow)
│   │   ├── dev/                      dev tools (claude_tools, dev_tools, patch_*, benchmarks)
│   │   ├── wake/                     wake-word detection + clips/ training samples
│   │   ├── web/                      Flask templates/ + static/ (consolidated)
│   │   ├── mcp_servers/              MCP server for dnd-app data
│   │   ├── ide_app/                  embedded web IDE (self-contained sub-app)
│   │   ├── kiosk/                    systemd service files
│   │   ├── scripts/                  deploy scripts (cloudflare, tailscale)
│   │   ├── tests/                    pytest suite (all test_*.py files live here)
│   │   ├── data/                     canonical data dir (content + runtime state)
│   │   ├── config/                   gitignored secrets
│   │   ├── requirements.txt, requirements-test.txt, pytest.ini
│   ├── docker/                       systemd services + docker-compose
│   ├── docs/                         BMO-specific docs (ARCHITECTURE, NETWORK_ACCESS, CLOUDFLARE_TUNNEL_SETUP)
│   └── {setup-bmo.sh, finalize-ssd.sh, .env.template}
│
├── docs/                             monorepo-wide docs
│   ├── ARCHITECTURE.md               how dnd-app + bmo communicate
│   ├── DATA-FLOW.md                  data location/flow
│   ├── SETUP.md                      clone + first-run
│   ├── COMMANDS.md                   command cheat sheet
│   ├── GLOSSARY.md                   beginner term index
│   ├── BACKUP.md                     backup strategy
│   ├── SECURITY.md           post-purge rotation guide
│   └── ISSUES-LOG.md               living bug log (AI agents APPEND here)
│
├── _archive/                         quarantined dead code (not deletion)
├── .github/                          workflows + issue templates + copilot-instructions.md
├── AGENTS.md, CLAUDE.md, GEMINI.md   AI agent instructions (tool-specific)
└── {README.md, .gitignore, .gitattributes, LICENSE, CONTRIBUTING.md, SECURITY.md, CHANGELOG.md}
```

## Core Principles

1. **Flat > Nested** — one subdir level is fine, two+ needs justification
2. **Feature > Type** — group by what it does, not what kind of file it is
3. **Canonical paths** — `/home/patrick/home-lab/bmo/pi/...` is the ONLY BMO location (no more `~/bmo/`)
4. **Preserve running state** — BMO systemd services run 24/7, restart required after path changes
5. **Secrets never tracked** — `.env`, `*.pem`, `*token*.json`, `credentials.json` in .gitignore
6. **_archive/ over deletion** — prefer quarantine when unsure

## Working in dnd-app/

- **Commands always from `dnd-app/`**: `cd dnd-app && npm run dev|build|test|lint`
- **Framework**: electron-vite (DO NOT change src/ layout — framework enforces)
- **Aliases**: `@renderer` → `src/renderer/src`, `@data` → `src/renderer/public/data`
- **Tests**: `.test.ts` colocated with source. Run with `vitest`.
- **Types**: TS strict. Zod for runtime validation.
- **State**: zustand stores in `src/renderer/src/stores/`
- **Linter**: biome (config at dnd-app/biome.json). Run `npm run lint`.
- **Plugin system**: game systems registered via `src/renderer/src/systems/registry.ts`

## Working in bmo/

- **Commands from `bmo/pi/`**: `cd bmo/pi && ./venv/bin/python app.py` (for dev)
- **Python 3.11** with venv at `bmo/pi/venv/` (gitignored)
- **Imports**: always use subpackage prefix — `from services.calendar_service import X` (NOT `from calendar_service import X`)
- **discord.py library**: import as `import discord` — our bots live in `bots/` package, NEVER rename to `discord/` (shadows library)
- **Data paths**: `~/home-lab/bmo/pi/data/...` (canonical). NEVER `~/bmo/...`
- **Tests**: pytest in `bmo/pi/tests/` (incl. test_*.py that were at pi/ root)
- **Running services**: `bmo, bmo-fan, bmo-kiosk, bmo-dm-bot, bmo-social-bot`
- **Restart after Python changes**: `sudo systemctl restart bmo` (+ bots if changed)

## Cross-domain (dnd-app ↔ bmo)

- dnd-app talks to BMO via HTTP on `http://bmo.local:5000` (configurable via `BMO_PI_URL` env)
- BMO Discord bots push events back to dnd-app via HTTP on port 5001 (dnd-app listens)
- Protocol docs: `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`
- IPC channel reference: `dnd-app/docs/IPC-SURFACE.md`

## Logging Bugs / Issues / Future Work

The log (`docs/ISSUES-LOG.md`) is for **unfixed or deferred** work that crosses session boundaries.

- **Fixing in this session?** → Just fix it. The commit is the record. Do NOT log — it clutters the log with already-resolved entries.
- **Out of scope / deferred?** → APPEND. Don't silently fix preexisting issues outside current task — log them, let user prioritize.
- **Log minor/optional items too** *(when out of scope)* — patterns across small observations reveal larger problems.
- **Read `docs/LOG-INSTRUCTIONS.md`** for the template + severity/category guide + the "log vs fix inline" decision rule with examples.

## Secrets / Safety

- Never commit `.env`, `credentials.json`, `token.json`, `*.pem`
- `.gitignore` has broad glob patterns catching these across the tree
- Pre-push secret-scanning hooks are a future improvement (see ISSUES-LOG)

## Git Conventions

- **Branches**: `feature/...`, `fix/...`, `docs/...`, `chore/...`
- **Commits**: imperative mood, summary ≤ 72 chars
- **Prefer small focused PRs** over mega-commits
- **Always `git status` before committing** — check no secrets leak

## For AI Sessions

- Start by reading this file + AGENTS.md (or your tool-specific file)
- Check `docs/ISSUES-LOG.md` before starting new work
- When in doubt about structure, check this file first
- When in doubt about protocol, check `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`
- When debugging, check `bmo/docs/TROUBLESHOOTING.md` + `docs/ISSUES-LOG.md`
